cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use gmat-copilot in academic work, please cite it using the metadata below."
title: gmat-copilot
abstract: >-
  gmat-copilot is a model-agnostic Python library and CLI that turns a natural-language request into
  a GMAT mission script. Generation is retrieval-grounded in the GMAT documentation and validated
  against a static linter, through a provider abstraction with no default model. Generation and
  validation need no GMAT install.
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Dimitrije
    family-names: Jankovic
version: 0.3.0
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/astro-tools/gmat-copilot"
url: "https://github.com/astro-tools/gmat-copilot"
keywords:
  - gmat
  - llm
  - code-generation
  - astrodynamics
  - mission-analysis
